Resistance Item											CLASSES:Artificer=1									SCHOOL:Abjuration		COMPS:S, M			CASTTIME:1 round			RANGE:Touch		TARGETAREA:Item touched																																				DURATION:10 min./level					SAVEINFO:None						SPELLRES:No						SOURCELONG:Eberron Campaign Setting	SOURCESHORT:ECS		SOURCEPAGE:p.114	DESC:A nonmagical item imbued with this infusion grants a +1 resistance bonus on saving throws to a character who wears or wields it. This bonus increases by 1 for every four caster levels (to +2 at 4th level, +3 at 8th level, +4 at 12th level, and so forth). Material Component: Oil mixed with various spices and minerals.
Shield of Faith, Legion's			KEY:Shield of Faith (Legion's)	CLASSES:Artificer,Cleric=4								SCHOOL:Abjuration											RANGE:Medium	TARGETAREA:Allied creatures in a 20-ft.-radius burst																																																						SOURCELONG:Eberron Campaign Setting	SOURCESHORT:ECS		SOURCEPAGE:p.115	DESC:This spell functions like shield of faith (see page 278 of the Player's Handbook), except that it affects multiple allies at a distance.
Skill Enhancement											CLASSES:Artificer=1									SCHOOL:Transmutation	COMPS:S, M			CASTTIME:1 round			RANGE:Touch		TARGETAREA:Item touched																																				DURATION:10 min./level					SAVEINFO:None						SPELLRES:No						SOURCELONG:Eberron Campaign Setting	SOURCESHORT:ECS		SOURCEPAGE:p.115	DESC:An item imbued with this infusion grants a +2 circumstance bonus on a specific skill check (determined by the caster) to a character who wears or wields it. This bonus increases by 1 for every two caster levels (to +3 at 2nd level, +4 at 4th level, +5 at 6th level, and so forth). Material Component: A length of fine, black thread.
Spell Storing Item										CLASSES:Artificer=1									SCHOOL:Transmutation	COMPS:S, XP (see text)	CASTTIME:1 minute			RANGE:Touch		TARGETAREA:Item touched																																				DURATION:1 hour/level or until discharged		SAVEINFO:None (object)					SPELLRES:No (object)				SOURCELONG:Eberron Campaign Setting	SOURCESHORT:ECS		SOURCEPAGE:p.115	DESC:This infusion allows you to place a spell effect into an item to draw it forth later, at your command. The item becomes, in effect, a wand with a single charge, which only you can use. You can imbue any spell of 4th level or lower into the item, as long as its spell level is no greater than one-half your artificer level. Your artificer level is the spell's caster level. You must make a successful Use Magic Device check (DC 20 + [spell level ? 3]) to emulate the spell and store it in the item. If you fail this check by 10 or more, you suffer a m ishap. T he DM determines t he r esult of a mishap, as with scroll mishaps. As a default, either the spell is activated immediately instead of being placed in the item, affecting you if possible, or the spell erupts in a burst of uncontrolled energy, dealing 2d6 points of damage to you. A single item can carry only one spell at a time. You must provide any expensive material components or XP component the spell requires at the time you imbue it into the item. You must provide any focus the spell requires at the time you cast it from the item. XP Cost: Your caster level ? the spell level. For example, to place a scorching ray spell in an item, you must spend XP equal to your caster level x 2.
Stone Construct											CLASSES:Artificer=3									SCHOOL:Transmutation	COMPS:S, M			CASTTIME:1 round			RANGE:Touch		TARGETAREA:Construct touched																																			DURATION:10 min./level or until discharged	SAVEINFO:Will negates (harmless)			SPELLRES:Yes (harmless)				SOURCELONG:Eberron Campaign Setting	SOURCESHORT:ECS		SOURCEPAGE:p.116	DESC:The construct you touch gains resistance to blows, cuts, stabs, and slashes. The subject gains damage reduction 10/adamantine. Once the spell has prevented a total of 10 points of damage per artificer level you possess (maximum 150 points), it is discharged. Material Component: Granite and 250 gp worth of diamond dust sprinkled on the construct.
Suppress Requirement										CLASSES:Artificer=3									SCHOOL:Transmutation	COMPS:S, M			CASTTIME:1 round			RANGE:Touch		TARGETAREA:Magic item touched																																			DURATION:10 min./level					SAVEINFO:Will negates (object)			SPELLRES:Yes (object)				SOURCELONG:Eberron Campaign Setting	SOURCESHORT:ECS		SOURCEPAGE:p.116	DESC:You alter a magic item that requires a certain class feature, race, ability score, or alignment to function to its fullest potential, so that it no longer carries that requirement. You must make a Use Magic Device check sufficient to emulate the requirement as if you were attempting to use the item yourself. If you succeed, the requirement is suppressed for the duration of this infusion. Material Component: Powdered gemstones worth a total of 500 gp.
Total Repair											CLASSES:Artificer=6									SCHOOL:Transmutation	COMPS:V, S			CASTTIME:1 standard action	RANGE:Touch		TARGETAREA:Construct touched	TARGETAREA:ability damage, blinded, confused, dazed, dazzled, deafened, feebleminded, and insanity. It also repairs 10 points of damage per level of the caster, to a maximum of 150 points at 15th level.	DURATION:Instantaneous					SAVEINFO:Will negates (harmless)			SPELLRES:Yes (harmless)				SOURCELONG:Eberron Campaign Setting	SOURCESHORT:ECS		SOURCEPAGE:p.116	DESC:Total repair enables you to transmute the structure of a construct to wipe away damage and afflictions. It immediately ends any and all of the following adverse conditions affecting the
Toughen Construct											CLASSES:Artificer=2									SCHOOL:Transmutation	COMPS:V, S			CASTTIME:1 standard action	RANGE:Touch		TARGETAREA:Construct touched																																			DURATION:10 min./level					SAVEINFO:None						SPELLRES:Yes (harmless)				SOURCELONG:Eberron Campaign Setting	SOURCESHORT:ECS		SOURCEPAGE:p.116	DESC:Toughen construct thickens the unliving matter that forms a construct's skin. The effect grants a +2 enhancement bonus to the creature's existing natural armor bonus. This enhancement bonus increases by 1 for every three caster levels above 3rd, to a maximum of +5 at caster level 12th. The enhancement bonus provided by toughen construct stacks with the target's natural armor bonus, but not with other enhancement bonuses to natural armor. A creature without natural armor has an effective natural armor bonus of +0.
